00:42:58,760 --> 00:43:00,000
{\fnCambria\fs22\1c&H45DFEC&\i1}- Science. - Science.

363
00:43:03,040 --> 00:43:05,080
{\fnCambria\fs22\1c&H45DFEC&\i1}As mayor of New Holland,

364
00:43:05,920 --> 00:43:09,040
{\fnCambria\fs22\1c&H45DFEC&\i1}you have entrusted me with your safety.

365
00:43:09,640 --> 00:43:14,960
{\fnCambria\fs22\1c&H45DFEC&\i1}So I can't sit idly while a teacher endangers our children.

366
00:43:15,520 --> 00:43:17,520
{\fnCambria\fs22\1c&H45DFEC&\i1}The man is a menace!

367
00:43:18,480 --> 00:43:20,520
{\fnCambria\fs22\1c&H45DFEC&\i1}She's right! He's crazy!

368
00:43:20,600 --> 00:43:23,330
{\fnCambria\fs22\1c&H45DFEC&\i1}Have you looked through this science book they're using?

369
00:43:23,560 --> 00:43:27,160
{\fnCambria\fs22\1c&H45DFEC&\i1}Apparently Pluto isn't good enough to be a planet any more.

370
00:43:27,560 --> 00:43:29,600
{\fnCambria\fs22\1c&H45DFEC&\i1}When I was a kid, Pluto was a great planet.

371
00:43:29,680 --> 00:43:31,680
{\fnCambria\fs22\1c&H45DFEC&\i1}This guy comes along and rewrites the rules!

372
00:43:31,760 --> 00:43:34,730
{\fnCambria\fs22\1c&H45DFEC&\i1}In fairness, he didn't write the textbook.

373
00:43:34,840 --> 00:43:37,880
{\fnCambria\fs22\1c&H45DFEC&\i1}Mr. Mayor, Edward Frankenstein.

374
00:43:38,440 --> 00:43:40,040
{\fnCambria\fs22\1c&H45DFEC&\i1}- Your neighbor, of course.

375
00:43:40,200 --> 00:43:42,800
{\fnCambria\fs22\1c&H45DFEC&\i1}I just would like to say that our son Victor

376
00:43:42,880 --> 00:43:45,960
{\fnCambria\fs22\1c&H45DFEC&\i1}is just crazy about the new teacher.

377
00:43:46,560 --> 00:43:47,680
{\fnCambria\fs22\1c&H45DFEC&\i1}Thinks he's great.

378
00:43:50,160 --> 00:43:51,760
{\fnCambria\fs22\1c&H45DFEC&\i1}My Cynthia has been asking

379
00:43:51,840 --> 00:43:55,400
{\fnCambria\fs22\1c&H45DFEC&\i1}all sorts of strange questions about things I've never even heard of.

380
00:43:56,560 --> 00:43:59,680
{\fnCambria\fs22\1c&H45DFEC&\i1}Shouldn't we at least give the man a chance to explain himself?

381
00:44:00,560 --> 00:44:01,520
{\fnCambria\fs22\1c&H45DFEC&\i1}Yes.

382
00:44:01,600 --> 00:44:05,600
{\fnCambria\fs22\1c&H45DFEC&\i1}Please come up, Mr. Menace.

383
00:44:26,360 --> 00:44:29,010
{\fnCambria\fs22\1c&H45DFEC&\i1}Ladies, gentlemen.

384
00:44:30,000 --> 00:44:33,890
{\fnCambria\fs22\1c&H45DFEC&\i1}I think the confusion here is that you are all very ignorant.

385
00:44:35,640 --> 00:44:37,240
{\fnCambria\fs22\1c&H45DFEC&\i1}Is that right word, "ignorant"?

386
00:44:37,800 --> 00:44:41,950
{\fnCambria\fs22\1c&H45DFEC&\i1}I mean "stupid," "primitive," "unenlightened."

387
00:44:42,600 --> 00:44:46,760
{\fnCambria\fs22\1c&H45DFEC&\i1}You do not understand science, so you are afraid of it.

388
00:44:46,840 --> 00:44:49,920
{\fnCambria\fs22\1c&H45DFEC&\i1}Like a dog is afraid of thunder or balloons.

389
00:44:50,040 --> 00:44:55,280
{\fnCambria\fs22\1c&H45DFEC&\i1}To you, science is magic and witchcraft because you have such small minds.

390
00:44:58,080 --> 00:45:00,440
{\fnCambria\fs22\1c&H45DFEC&\i1}I cannot make your heads bigger,

391
00:45:00,520 --> 00:45:04,980
{\fnCambria\fs22\1c&H45DFEC&\i1}but your children's heads, I can take them and crack them open.

392
00:45:05,920 --> 00:45:10,280
{\fnCambria\fs22\1c&H45DFEC&\i1}This is what I try to do, to get at their brains!

393
00:45:12,880 --> 00:45:14,000
{\fnCambria\fs22\1c&H45DFEC&\i1}Oh, my.

394
00:45:15,680 --> 00:45:16,840
{\fnCambria\fs22\1c&H45DFEC&\i1}Thank you.

395
00:45:20,320 --> 00:45:21,760
{\fnCambria\fs22\1c&H45DFEC&\i1}Oh, jeez.

396
00:45:24,640 --> 00:45:26,360
{\fnCambria\fs22\1c&H45DFEC&\i1}Be quick, boy. They'll be home any minute.

