00:46:00,120 --> 00:46:01,160
{\fnCambria\fs22\1c&H45DFEC&\i1}Victor?

406
00:46:01,240 --> 00:46:03,920
{\fnCambria\fs22\1c&H45DFEC&\i1}Hi, Elsa. What are you doing?

407
00:46:04,240 --> 00:46:06,200
{\fnCambria\fs22\1c&H45DFEC&\i1}Practicing my song for Dutch Day.

408
00:46:06,680 --> 00:46:07,680
{\fnCambria\fs22\1c&H45DFEC&\i1}It's nice.

409
00:46:07,760 --> 00:46:10,040
{\fnCambria\fs22\1c&H45DFEC&\i1}- Did you get a new dog? - No.

410
00:46:10,160 --> 00:46:13,050
{\fnCambria\fs22\1c&H45DFEC&\i1}- I heard a bark. - Yeah, that was me.

411
00:46:13,600 --> 00:46:15,170
{\fnCambria\fs22\1c&H45DFEC&\i1}You are barking?

412
00:46:21,200 --> 00:46:23,600
{\fnCambria\fs22\1c&H45DFEC&\i1}Hmm. You must really miss Sparky.

413
00:46:29,040 --> 00:46:31,200
{\fnCambria\fs22\1c&H45DFEC&\i1}Uh, I got to go. Bye.

414
00:46:32,680 --> 00:46:33,720
{\fnCambria\fs22\1c&H45DFEC&\i1}Bye.

415
00:46:38,120 --> 00:46:41,120
{\fnCambria\fs22\1c&H45DFEC&\i1}I feel so sad for him, Persephone.

416
00:46:41,200 --> 00:46:43,120
{\fnCambria\fs22\1c&H45DFEC&\i1}He really misses his dog.

417
00:46:51,800 --> 00:46:53,560
{\fnCambria\fs22\1c&H45DFEC&\i1}Where's Mr. Rzykruski?

418
00:46:53,640 --> 00:46:56,680
{\fnCambria\fs22\1c&H45DFEC&\i1}All I know is I'll be teaching the class for the rest of the semester.

419
00:46:57,000 --> 00:46:59,000
{\fnCambria\fs22\1c&H45DFEC&\i1}Do you know anything about science?

420
00:46:59,320 --> 00:47:00,730
{\fnCambria\fs22\1c&H45DFEC&\i1}I know more than you do.

421
00:47:01,000 --> 00:47:02,490
{\fnCambria\fs22\1c&H45DFEC&\i1}Mr. Rzykruski knew a lot.

422
00:47:03,720 --> 00:47:06,690
{\fnCambria\fs22\1c&H45DFEC&\i1}Well, sometimes knowing too much is the problem.

423
00:47:07,600 --> 00:47:09,120
{\fnCambria\fs22\1c&H45DFEC&\i1}What about the science fair?

424
00:47:09,360 --> 00:47:12,920
{\fnCambria\fs22\1c&H45DFEC&\i1}Oh, it's still on, but it will be judged by someone who's not insane!

425
00:47:13,000 --> 00:47:14,000
{\fnCambria\fs22\1c&H45DFEC&\i1}Me!

426
00:47:14,080 --> 00:47:16,360
{\fnCambria\fs22\1c&H45DFEC&\i1}Now get cracking, and may the best person win!

427
00:47:20,840 --> 00:47:23,240
{\fnCambria\fs22\1c&H45DFEC&\i1}I can't believe they let the gym teacher be the judge.

428
00:47:24,080 --> 00:47:26,080
{\fnCambria\fs22\1c&H45DFEC&\i1}She's not even interested in science.

429
00:47:26,480 --> 00:47:29,450
{\fnCambria\fs22\1c&H45DFEC&\i1}Back home, everyone is scientist.

430
00:47:29,640 --> 00:47:32,920
{\fnCambria\fs22\1c&H45DFEC&\i1}Even my plumber wins Nobel Prize.

431
00:47:33,000 --> 00:47:35,970
{\fnCambria\fs22\1c&H45DFEC&\i1}Your country does not make enough scientist.

432
00:47:36,080 --> 00:47:37,880
{\fnCambria\fs22\1c&H45DFEC&\i1}Always needs more.

433
00:47:38,000 --> 00:47:40,400
{\fnCambria\fs22\1c&H45DFEC&\i1}You should be a scientist, Victor.

434
00:47:40,600 --> 00:47:42,170
{\fnCambria\fs22\1c&H45DFEC&\i1}Nobody likes scientists.

435
00:47:42,520 --> 00:47:46,570
{\fnCambria\fs22\1c&H45DFEC&\i1}They like what science gives them, but not the questions, no.

