441
00:48:05,360 --> 00:48:07,930
{\fnCambria\fs22\1c&H45DFEC&\i1}I mean, it sort of worked, but then it didn't.

442
00:48:08,080 --> 00:48:09,490
{\fnCambria\fs22\1c&H45DFEC&\i1}And I don't know why.

443
00:48:09,840 --> 00:48:13,280
{\fnCambria\fs22\1c&H45DFEC&\i1}Then maybe you never really understood it the first time.

444
00:48:13,800 --> 00:48:19,120
{\fnCambria\fs22\1c&H45DFEC&\i1}People think science is here, but it is also here.

445
00:48:20,320 --> 00:48:23,130
{\fnCambria\fs22\1c&H45DFEC&\i1}The first time, did you love your experiment?

446
00:48:23,480 --> 00:48:24,640
{\fnCambria\fs22\1c&H45DFEC&\i1}Yes.

447
00:48:25,640 --> 00:48:26,760
{\fnCambria\fs22\1c&H45DFEC&\i1}Ah.

448
00:48:29,640 --> 00:48:31,400
{\fnCambria\fs22\1c&H45DFEC&\i1}And the second time?

449
00:48:36,640 --> 00:48:39,210
{\fnCambria\fs22\1c&H45DFEC&\i1}No. I just wanted it over.

450
00:48:39,760 --> 00:48:42,160
{\fnCambria\fs22\1c&H45DFEC&\i1}Then you changed the variables.

451
00:48:42,680 --> 00:48:44,520
{\fnCambria\fs22\1c&H45DFEC&\i1}I was doing it for the wrong reason.

452
00:48:44,600 --> 00:48:47,760
{\fnCambria\fs22\1c&H45DFEC&\i1}Science is not good or bad, Victor.

453
00:48:48,640 --> 00:48:51,120
{\fnCambria\fs22\1c&H45DFEC&\i1}But it can be used both ways.

454
00:48:51,680 --> 00:48:55,680
